{
  "_comment": [
    "Manual/editorial source of truth for the mbo/hash README tables, rendered by",
    "`hash_benchmark_report.py quality`. This holds ONLY human-authored per-instance",
    "data; the measured columns (SMHasher3 verdict/score/failing families) are NOT",
    "here - they come from a data bundle (`quality --bundle`), joined by `smhasher` name.",
    "One entry per (algorithm, width) instance, so both README tables separate 64/128",
    "consistently (murmur3 is 128-only: its GetHash64 is the folded 128; xxh3 is native",
    "at both). `starlark` marks a hash also ported in //mbo/hash:hash.bzl. Edit here;",
    "run `quality` to re-render."
  ],
